'For me, it was a dream to play in the Premier League. I always wanted to be here because this league is very good, it has very good teams and Manchester United is the best team in England.'

Falcao joins from Monaco where he scored 13 goals in 22 appearances last season before a knee injury ruled him out of the 2014 World Cup.

United fans had to wait until 1:30am on Tuesday morning for Falcao to be officially unveiled after a day which saw the Colombian arrive at Manchester airport shortly before 6pm as the Red Devils smashed the £160m barrier for the summer of spending under Van Gaal.

